This paper focuses on human-robot teaming, decision-making, and task management, which are all related to robotics (cs.RO). The use of regret emotion and its influence on decision-making also falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The optimization of queuing requests from multiple robots can be categorized under multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and the balancing of workload and performance in the team can be related to control systems (cs.SY).
